s/recharts)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":7,"content":"[![npm downloads](https://img.shields.io/npm/dm/recharts.svg?style=flat-square)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/recharts)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":12,"content":"Recharts is a **Redefined** chart library built with [React](https://facebook.github.io/react/) and [D3](http://d3js.org).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":14,"content":"The main purpose of this library is to help you to write charts in React applications without any pain. Main principles of Recharts are:","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":20,"content":"Documentation at [recharts.org](https://recharts.org) and our [storybook](https://recharts.org/en-US/storybook)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":22,"content":"Also see [the wiki](https://github.com/recharts/recharts/wiki).","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":38,"content":"All the components of Recharts are clearly separated. The LineChart is composed of x axis, tooltip, grid, and line items, and each of them is an independent React Component. The clear separation and composition of components is one of the principle Recharts follows.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":44,"content":"NPM is the easiest and fastest way to get started using Recharts. It is also the recommended installation method when building single-page applications (SPAs). It pairs nicely with a CommonJS module bundler such as Webpack.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":48,"content":"$ npm install recharts react-is","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":61,"content":"<script src=\"https://unpkg.com/recharts/umd/Recharts.min.js\"></script>","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":64,"content":"Then you can find the library on `window.Recharts`.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":68,"content":"Recharts is open source. If you want to contribute to the project, please read the [CONTRIBUTING.md](/CONTRIBUTING.md)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":86,"content":"Copyright (c) 2015-2024 Recharts Group.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false}]},{"file":"./apps/web/node_modules/recharts/DEVELOPING.md","matches":[{"lineNumber":4,"content":"$ git clone https://github.com/recharts/recharts.git","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":5,"content":"$ cd recharts","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":103,"content":"[Releases](https://github.com/recharts/recharts/releases) are automated via GH Actions - when a new release is created","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":117,"content":"1. Make your changes in recharts","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":118,"content":"2. `yalc publish` in recharts","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":119,"content":"3. `yalc add recharts` in your test package (ex: in a vite or webpack reach app with recharts installed, imported, and","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false}]},{"file":"./apps/web/node_modules/recharts/CONTRIBUTING.md","matches":[{"lineNumber":1,"content":"# Contributing to Recharts","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":3,"content":"We'd love for you to contribute to our source code and to make Recharts even better than it is today!","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":11,"content":"We use Github Discussion to organize our discussion along new initiatives and organize ourselves. Please do check the [announcements](https://github.com/recharts/recharts/discussions/categories/announcements) section for an overview of recent initiatives.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":13,"content":"Also feel free to join us on Slack: https://recharts.slack.com/archives/C042Q5K5UDC","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":19,"content":"We will be using [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/recharts/recharts/issues) for our bugs and feature requests. We will keep a close eye on this and try to make it clear when we have an internal fix in progress. Before filing a new task, try to make sure your problem doesn't already exist.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":23,"content":"The best way to get your bug fixed is to provide a reduced test case. codesandbox provide a way to give live examples. You can fork our example in [recharts.org](http://recharts.org/) to show your case.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":59,"content":"- Search [GitHub](https://github.com/recharts/recharts/pulls) for an open or closed Pull Request that relates to your submission. You don't want to duplicate effort.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":76,"content":"By contributing to Recharts, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under its MIT license.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false}]},{"file":"./apps/web/node_modules/recharts/CHANGELOG.md","matches":[{"lineNumber":1,"content":"## ⚠️ Next versions change notes are available only on the [GitHub Releases](https://github.com/recharts/recharts/releases) page ⚠️","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":55,"content":"- fix: fix \"recharts@… doesn't provide prop-types, requested by react-smooth\" warning (#2895)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":148,"content":"- Axis scale=band no longer works as of Recharts 2.x.x (#2742)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":234,"content":"- Fix for recharts issue #1787","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":504,"content":"- revert [PR#1916](https://github.com/recharts/recharts/pull/1916)","contentTruncated":false,"isContex